Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.79,0:00:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,DÜSSELDORF METROPOLITAN POLICE\NHOLDING CELLS
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.30,0:00:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell Helene and Gustav to record\NDetective Forster for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.30,0:00:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.22,0:00:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,They play reruns of it\Nevery Tuesday at 10 a.m.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.10,0:00:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Ain't you seen it? It's a great show!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.31,0:00:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Milch, this isn't the time\Nto be messing around.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.94,0:00:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have any idea how much trouble
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.69,0:00:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you caused the boss\Nwhen you screwed up and got caught?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.28,0:00:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though you're such a dimwit,\Nhe still sent me to be your lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.54,0:00:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Show the boss some appreciation.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.96,0:00:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He just sent you to make sure\Nthat I don't blab everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.17,0:00:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. Now listen, Milch.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.34,0:00:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You do know\Nwhat will happen if you talk, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.14,0:00:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't get your shorts in a knot.\NI'd never backstab my buddies.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.89,0:00:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine, I'll believe you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.81,0:01:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Now just confess according to\Nthe script I've given you. Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.44,0:01:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm more interested in knowing\Nwhen my next job will be.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.98,0:01:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Your next job? Don't you know\Nhow long you're going to be in?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.32,0:01:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Get real!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.49,0:01:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,-You're the ones who need to get real.\N-Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.53,0:01:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Just who do you think I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.95,0:01:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Gunther Milch,\Nthe king of prison breaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.00,0:01:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have time for your garbage.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.42,0:01:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen. If you confess according to\Nmy script, you'll get out in five years.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.30,0:01:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,-Make sure you tell them.\N-Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.93,0:01:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I just said,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.18,0:01:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,tell Helene and Gustav\Nto record Detective Forster.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.44,0:01:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But those guys aren't very reliable.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.19,0:01:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I should probably try\None more time while I'm at this station.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.40,0:01:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Try what?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.13,0:03:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet he's faking it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.50,0:03:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.63,0:03:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,There was blood in his vomit\Nand he feels really cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.39,0:03:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,-Don't puke here!\N-Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.43,0:03:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You have good timing!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.68,0:03:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I need you to watch this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.69,0:03:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Some young punks who were arrested\Nstarted a riot on the third floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.23,0:03:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people got injured.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.57,0:03:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But this guy looks like he's about to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.49,0:03:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Milch again, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.11,0:03:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Put him on that bed.\NI'll check him out later.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.87,0:04:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,No way! Take me to the hospital!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.79,0:04:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be back soon. Just sit tight.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.75,0:04:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn, the sick people just keep coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.51,0:04:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to be kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.47,0:04:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell's\Nthat serial killer doing in the next bed?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.77,0:04:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Quit whining!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.73,0:04:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He collapsed because he hasn't been\Neating, so I gave him an IV.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.07,0:04:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That guy being near me\Nis just making me even sicker!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.20,0:04:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up and lie still!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.62,0:04:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, you said people were injured.\NHow many are there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.70,0:04:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,How should I know?\NI won't know till I get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.16,0:04:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Dammit!\NI'll make those young punks pay later!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.34,0:04:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,About what you said before…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.84,0:05:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.64,0:05:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.98,0:05:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I'm going to kill…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.90,0:05:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,your ex-fiancée, Eva Heinemann.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.33,0:05:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.16,0:05:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't you agree that it's a good idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.75,0:05:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, she knows far too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.88,0:05:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,On that rainy day, she was\Nat the building under construction.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.80,0:05:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,She heard three shots fired and saw…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.14,0:05:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.60,0:05:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't need people like her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.93,0:05:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't, do we?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.60,0:05:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.15,0:05:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.15,0:05:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.77,0:06:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,She… Eva would never testify to that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.03,0:06:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,All she wants is\Nfor me to be thrown in prison forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.82,0:06:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,She simply wants me to regret\Ndumping her for the rest of my life!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.62,0:06:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,She'll only testify\Nto things that'll hurt me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.83,0:06:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So… that's why…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.04,0:06:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's why I asked you\Nif you agreed that it was a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.09,0:06:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,With her out of the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.01,0:06:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you could get out of going to prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.06,0:06:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be very good for us,\Nas well as for you if she died.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.57,0:06:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to tell the cops?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.11,0:06:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think they'd believe\Nthat kind of story?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.53,0:06:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Or are you going to tell\Nthe lawyer Mr. Verdemann?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.74,0:06:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He and I might be working together,\Nyou know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.17,0:07:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We talented lawyers will\Nget you pronounced innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.63,0:07:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you're cleared and get out,\Nyou'll be able to enjoy a nice drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.35,0:07:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,By that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.14,0:07:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that miserable, stuck up,\Nloud-mouthed has-been will be long gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.29,0:07:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.38,0:07:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You got to be kidding me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.42,0:07:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I ain't lying next\Nto this goddamn murderer!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.63,0:07:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Milch! Shut your trap!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.51,0:07:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What do I care if you never\Nconfess to your murders!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.81,0:07:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Milch!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.72,0:07:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I confessed up to what I did,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.85,0:07:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and now I'll get sent to jail\Nwithin five days!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.77,0:08:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad I won't have to be stuck\Nwith a murderer like you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.07,0:08:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,-Quit your damn shouting!\N-Milch!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.61,0:08:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You're perfectly healthy!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.32,0:08:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Come with us! I knew you were faking it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.86,0:08:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I can hardly wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.82,0:08:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I've only got to put up with\Nfive more days with this goddamn murderer!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.25,0:08:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.87,0:08:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up, dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.68,0:08:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Within five days, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.77,0:08:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,On that rainy day,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.10,0:08:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you heard three shots fired\Nin a building that was under construction
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.77,0:08:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and saw a young blonde man\Ncome down the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.90,0:08:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That's correct, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.78,0:08:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.87,0:08:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,How about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.99,0:08:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you still plan on ignoring\Nthe existence of Johan?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.91,0:08:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.29,0:09:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Eva Heinemann,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.88,0:09:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,will you testify to this in court?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.81,0:09:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.15,0:09:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,DÜSSELDORF METROPOLITAN POLICE
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.32,0:09:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think Dr. Tenma wants\Nto talk to us this late at night for?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.66,0:09:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does he want to talk now?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.16,0:09:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know. But he said\Nhe had to talk to the investigators.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.96,0:09:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it you want to tell us, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.68,0:09:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,In Düsseldorf at Eisler Memorial Hospital,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.10,0:09:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Director Heinemann…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.44,0:10:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Director of Surgery Oppenheimer,\NDr. Boyer…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.69,0:10:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and my patient, Adolf Junkers…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.66,0:10:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I… killed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.01,0:10:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I… killed all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.11,0:10:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The wind blew.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.40,0:10:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The thermos tumbled over.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.15,0:10:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The sandwiches got covered in dirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.87,0:11:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.38,0:11:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,smiled sadly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.88,0:11:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,According to a police announcement,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.05,0:11:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in the early hours of the fourth,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.43,0:11:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the suspect Kenzo Tenma,\Nwho had denied his guilt
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.51,0:11:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in all the murder charges against him,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.56,0:11:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,has changed his story\Nregarding the murders
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.77,0:11:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,at Eisler Memorial Hospital\Nin Düsseldorf of the hospital director,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.94,0:11:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,two other doctors, and Adolf Junkers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.19,0:11:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He has confessed to all their killings.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.78,0:11:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.16,0:11:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,This news is just in.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.62,0:11:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,He confessed? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.62,0:11:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,…in the early hours of the fourth,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.08,0:11:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the suspect Kenzo Tenma,\Nwho had denied his guilt
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.63,0:11:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in all the murder charges against him,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.54,0:11:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,has confessed that he perpetrated\Nall the crimes he's charged with.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.84,0:11:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't stand for this!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.72,0:12:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What the heck did you do to Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.93,0:12:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of torture did you\Nput him through
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.27,0:12:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to get him to confess to crimes\Nhe didn't commit?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.06,0:12:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you let go of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.31,0:12:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough of this!\NI demand to see Tenma right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.57,0:12:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll talk to him myself and find out
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.90,0:12:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,what you put him through\Nduring interrogation!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.36,0:12:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's pointless, Dr. Reichwein.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.37,0:12:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.50,0:12:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He won't even let me,\Nhis own lawyer, see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.75,0:12:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It appears that he confessed\Nto the crimes all on his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.55,0:12:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just not possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.68,0:12:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked around.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.80,0:12:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I know the investigators.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.76,0:12:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They could never torture anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.60,0:12:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Tenma confessed quite easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.81,0:12:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So easily, it was surprising.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.81,0:12:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Verdemann!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.44,0:12:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me even you think\Nthat his confession is genuine!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.28,0:13:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless I can interview him,\NI won't know why he's done this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.41,0:13:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe in him!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.46,0:13:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma is innocent!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.21,0:13:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe in him!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.56,0:13:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello? Verdemann here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.73,0:13:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Mr. Baul.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.61,0:13:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm terribly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.73,0:13:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Something suddenly came up\Nso I couldn't go with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.57,0:13:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.07,0:13:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,How did it go?\NDid Dr. Tenma really confess?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.16,0:13:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, he also refused to see me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.08,0:13:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a real pity.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.83,0:13:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We, lawyers, were working so hard\Nto prove his innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.66,0:13:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and that he was falsely accused,\Nbut then he goes and confesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.30,0:14:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,In that regard,\Nyour father was very admirable.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.84,0:14:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how harsh\Nthe interrogations were,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.76,0:14:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,he never succumbed,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.89,0:14:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and always claimed his innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.35,0:14:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And he was innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.81,0:14:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So then, what would you like\Nto do now, Mr. Verdemann?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.86,0:14:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Verdemann?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.03,0:14:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.36,0:14:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What about that woman?\NWhat was her name again?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.16,0:14:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That woman who can prove\NTenma's innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.41,0:14:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. Her name's Eva Heinemann.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.09,0:14:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is she now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.50,0:14:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,At a hotel in the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.59,0:14:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to talk to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.80,0:14:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd better not.\NShe's rather difficult to deal with.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.43,0:14:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll meet with her again, alone this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.82,0:14:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,My father was admirable, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.88,0:15:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Open up, Eva Heinemann.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.13,0:15:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you're inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.72,0:15:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The maids told me that you've been\Nin there drinking
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.72,0:15:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,all day long so they can't even\Nmake up the bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.81,0:15:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Heinemann,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.64,0:15:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I am fully aware\Nthat you despise Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.65,0:15:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Even after the loss of your father,\Nthe director,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.36,0:15:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,if your relationship\Nwith Dr. Tenma had continued,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.32,0:15:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you would have had a very satisfying life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.07,0:15:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Dr. Tenma left you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.08,0:15:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd agree that Dr. Tenma threw\Nyour life into turmoil.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.13,0:15:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,My father…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.79,0:16:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,My father was tossed into prison as a spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.63,0:16:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,For many years, I was shunned\Nand looked upon as the son of a spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.47,0:16:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,My life was\Nthrown into turmoil by my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.68,0:16:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But I didn't succumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.10,0:16:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know why?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.27,0:16:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know why I was able to fight back?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.52,0:16:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I believed in him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.49,0:16:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I believed my father was innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.53,0:16:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,My father was innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.28,0:16:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,My father was innocent!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.08,0:16:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Innocent…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.79,0:16:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The people I believe in must be innocent!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.50,0:16:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I will prove that Tenma is innocent!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.88,0:16:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Tenma must be innocent!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.47,0:16:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like my father\Nmust be innocent as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.65,0:17:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are me and my partner's\Nphone numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.44,0:17:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Contact us if you decide to testify.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.92,0:17:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that? He's being\Ntransferred to jail tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.97,0:17:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's only been a few days\Nsince he arrived!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.06,0:17:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because Tenma's confession\Nhas gone incredibly smoothly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.39,0:17:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't there anything you can do,\NMr. Verdemann?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.94,0:17:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the police are doing what they can\Nto convince Tenma to let us see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.24,0:17:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, where's Eva Heinemann?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.49,0:17:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,She went out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.70,0:17:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.74,0:17:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,She's probably getting blind drunk\Nat some bar again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.67,0:18:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Düsseldorf…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.13,0:18:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all the same stinking places.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.34,0:18:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.83,0:18:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.21,0:18:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been sitting here\Nfor the last five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.21,0:18:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.42,0:18:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a fascinating paper,\Nso I was copying it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.21,0:18:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't we go somewhere else?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.51,0:18:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, let's get something to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.26,0:19:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do you want to go?\NAn Italian place? Or maybe French?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.43,0:19:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,-Gee, don't let me bother you.\N-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.52,0:19:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You may as well keep copying it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.77,0:19:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait! Eva!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.15,0:19:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Eva!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.30,0:19:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad you like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.64,0:19:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty good, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.69,0:19:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.19,0:19:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, putting a stone here\Nwill keep it from blowing away.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.19,0:19:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not what I mean.\NWhy are you putting the blanket here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.49,0:19:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nice for a change\Nto have lunch in a place like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.74,0:20:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The weather's nice too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.78,0:20:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's having lunch here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.12,0:20:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We are. I made us sandwiches.\NI hope you like them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.67,0:20:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There are bugs everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.08,0:20:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.38,0:20:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This is ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.43,0:20:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,They're covered in dirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.23,0:20:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They're ruined.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.49,0:20:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You want one too, lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.75,0:20:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Franz, don't bother her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.41,0:20:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be rude!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.75,0:20:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.18,0:21:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Good, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.90,0:21:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.95,0:21:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Get in.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.67,0:21:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.92,0:21:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't able to get through\Nto Mr. Verdemann.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.55,0:21:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So I called you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.93,0:21:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,, I see.\NHis wife's about ready to give birth,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.89,0:21:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,so he's probably at the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.98,0:21:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He's told me about you though,\NEva Heinemann.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.56,0:21:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Feel free to ask me anything you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.15,0:21:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.90,0:22:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Do what?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.49,0:22:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll testify to prove Tenma's innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.95,0:22:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that right? That would be fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.08,0:22:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what hotel are you staying at?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.51,0:22:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.88,0:22:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be there right away.
